# Documentation scope (interactive-gltf-engine)

This repository holds **reference implementation**, **igltf-editor**, **Tauri packaging**, and **engineering docs**. Portable glTF extension and JS scripting **normative** text lives in **`interactive-gltf-specs`**, not here.

## Where to write documentation

| Topic | Location |
|-------|----------|
| igltf-editor UI, MCP, sessions, `project.json` | **`docs/`** (e.g. `docs/editor/`) |
| Backend HTTP/WS API, storage layout, exporter | **`docs/`** or **`igltf-editor-backend/docs/`** |
| Tauri / desktop build | **`tauri-build/README.md`**, **`docs/`** |
| Sketcher migration, ROADMAP items | **`docs/`**, **`ROADMAP.md`** |
| MCP authoring kit (operational script hints) | **`igltf-editor-backend/authoring_kit/`** |
| Component setup (dev server, env vars) | Component **`README.md`** |
| **Portable** glTF extensions + JS scripting language | **`interactive-gltf-specs`** (`proposals/`, `specifications/`) |

## Sync with specs (narrow trigger)

1. Document **full editor truth** in **`docs/editor/`** (this repo).
2. When behaviour **extends or diverges** from **`interactive-gltf-specs`**, create or update a **proposal** there (`sync-interactive-gltf-format-from-engine`).

Sync only when code changes **exported** asset meaning (glTF extensions, portable script bundle, shared host API). Editor-only fields stay in **`docs/editor/`**.

## Skills

- **`migrate-sketcher-feature`** — editor UI/UX parity; docs stay in **`docs/`** here.
- Spec skills (`create-gltf-extension`, `manage-proposal-open-issues`, …) — run in **interactive-gltf-specs**, not for editor proposals.
